    "body": "Ok it's not fully fixed yet:\r\n```console\r\n➜  foundry git:(master) ✗ cargo run --bin forge -- script --help | head -n 10\r\n    Finished dev [unoptimized] target(s) in 0.17s\r\n     Running `target/debug/forge script --help`\r\nforge-script\r\n`EvmArgs` and `EnvArgs` take the highest precedence in the Config/Figment hierarchy. All vars are\r\nopt-in, their default values are expected to be set by the [`foundry_config::Config`], and are\r\nalways present ([`foundry_config::Config::default`])\r\n\r\nBoth have corresponding types in the `evm_adapters` crate which have mandatory fields. The expected\r\nworkflow is 1. load the [`foundry_config::Config`] 2. merge with `EvmArgs` into a `figment::Figment`\r\n3. extract `evm_adapters::Opts` from the merged `Figment`\r\n\r\n# Example\r\n\r\n➜  foundry git:(master) ✗ cargo run --bin forge -- debug --help | head -n 10\r\n    Finished dev [unoptimized] target(s) in 0.17s\r\n     Running `target/debug/forge debug --help`\r\nforge-debug\r\n`EvmArgs` and `EnvArgs` take the highest precedence in the Config/Figment hierarchy. All vars are\r\nopt-in, their default values are expected to be set by the [`foundry_config::Config`], and are\r\nalways present ([`foundry_config::Config::default`])\r\n\r\nBoth have corresponding types in the `evm_adapters` crate which have mandatory fields. The expected\r\nworkflow is 1. load the [`foundry_config::Config`] 2. merge with `EvmArgs` into a `figment::Figment`\r\n3. extract `evm_adapters::Opts` from the merged `Figment`\r\n\r\n# Example\r\n```\r\n\r\nSome strange things are going on with clap flattening because applying this reordering changes solves the problem:\r\n<img width=\"553\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5773434/175131908-ed77f94a-e924-41f2-b605-aa0851b3bb4f.png\">\r\n",
